Key Match Events: Rain interrupted play, and the match was abandoned before England could begin their pursuit of a revised target of 109 in 10 overs.
Scotland made 90-0 in an interrupted innings reduced to 10 overs, with George Munsey 41 not out and Michael Jones 45 not out.
Post-Match Reflections: Both sides received a point apiece.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Rain led to the abandonment of the match.
